The Lagos State Sports Trust Fund (LSSTF) has donated sports equipment to the 644 public secondary schools in Lagos through the six education districts of the State. Table tennis boards, spikes, jerseys, balls, volleyball, relay batons, chess boards, scrabble equipment, as well as first aid boxes were among the equipment distributed to the schools. Speaking at the presentation of the sports equipment, Deputy Governor of Lagos State, Obafemi Hamzat, who was represented by the Permanent Secretary in the Office of the Deputy Governor, Mrs. Mojisola Daba said the gesture was aimed at restoring the glory of the state as the leading state in sports administration.   EPL: Awoniyi may lead Nottingham against Newcastle     Ferguson urges Rangers to keep Bassey     Federer eyes one more Wimbledon   “I urge all tutor generals/permanent secretaries, principals, and staff of all public schools in the six education districts to ensure the appropriate use of the distributed sports equipment appropriately to achieve the desired effect to the glory of Lagos State,” Hamzat reportedly said. Meanwhile, the Executive Chairman of the Lagos State Sports Commission (LSSC) Sola Aiyepeku, said LSSTF has been creating and uniting opportunities capable of diverting the attention of the youths from crimes to focusing on the development of school sports. At present, LSSTF is constructing an Olympic-size swimming pool, warm-up/training pool equipped with a 500-seater spectator stand at Rowe Park in two months, the project would be delivered. The Executive Secretary of LSSTF Olaposi Agunbiade advised the students to shun vices that can mar their future while calling on Lagosians and the private sector to support the Sports Trust Fund in other to reduce youths’ restiveness.